@node intro "Introduction"

@{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

Space - the final frontrier.... place where cliboard can live...
heh.. okidoki...

This litte utility has only one job to do. It will  help you with the
clipboard. How?
In this package you'll find 2 programs @{b}copy2clip@{ub} & @{b}Clip2File@{ub}
Copy2clip will copy the selected file to  the clipboard - it is usful when
you have some includes, or something else :) for clipping. Clip2file  will store
the contents of the clipboard to a file.

Ok? :-)
@endnode

@node usage "Usage"

@{b}@{u}Usage@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}Clip2File@{ub} <filename>

        where <filename> is file the clipboard will be saved to.

@{b}Copy2Clip@{ub} <filename>

        where <filename> is file that will be placed in the clipboard

@{b}Dopus command lines@{ub}

        AmigaDOS Workbench:C/Copy2Clip {F}
        AmigaDOS Workbench:C/Clip2file {RF}
@endnode

